# WHO WAS I ‚Äî Cline Project Rules
# Living memorial platform ‚Äî whowasi.uk

## Tech Stack
- React 19 + Vite + Tailwind CSS v4
- Framer Motion v12 (animations)
- React Router v7 (`createBrowserRouter`, loader pattern)
- InstantDB (`@instantdb/react`) ‚Äî real-time reactive database (no REST, no SQL)
- Vercel ‚Äî hosting + serverless API functions in `/api/*.js`
- Resend ‚Äî transactional email
- Cloudinary ‚Äî image hosting/CDN (upload via `src/lib/uploadImage.js`)
- Stripe ‚Äî subscriptions
- ElevenLabs ‚Äî voice synthesis (via `/api/elevenlabs.js` proxy ONLY)

---

## SECURITY ‚Äî READ FIRST

**NEVER put any API key in a `VITE_` prefixed variable.**
`VITE_` variables are bundled into the client and exposed publicly.

Only allowed `VITE_` vars:
- `VITE_INSTANT_APP_ID` ‚Äî InstantDB app ID (safe, public)
- `VITE_CLOUDINARY_CLOUD_NAME` ‚Äî Cloudinary cloud name (safe, public)

All other secrets (`RESEND_API_KEY`, `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`, `ELEVENLABS_API_KEY`,
`STRIPE_SECRET_KEY`, `STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET`) live **server-side only** in Vercel
environment variables and are used exclusively in `/api/*.js` files.

**Never import Anthropic, ElevenLabs, Resend, or Stripe SDKs in `src/`.**
Always proxy through `/api/*.js` serverless functions.

---

## InstantDB ‚Äî How We Use It

### Initialisation
```js
// src/lib/instant.js
import { init } from '@instantdb/react'
import schema from '../instant.schema'
export const db = init({ appId: import.meta.env.VITE_INSTANT_APP_ID, schema })
```

### Auth
```js
const { isLoading, user, error } = db.useAuth()
// user.id is the unique identifier throughout the codebase
```

### Queries
```js
// All queries are reactive ‚Äî component re-renders on data change
const { data, isLoading, error } = db.useQuery({
  memorials: { $: { where: { createdBy: user.id } } }
})
// One-shot (non-reactive):
const { data } = await db.queryOnce({ memorials: { $: { where: { id: memorialId } } } })
```

### Mutations
```js
import { id } from '@instantdb/react'
// Create
await db.transact(db.tx.memorials[id()].update({ name: 'Ada', createdBy: user.id, createdAt: Date.now() }))
// Update
await db.transact(db.tx.memorials[memorialId].update({ bio: 'new bio' }))
// Delete
await db.transact(db.tx.memorials[memorialId].delete())
// Link
await db.transact(db.tx.memorials[memId].link({ tributes: tributeId }))
```

### Query with $in
```js
// Filter by array of IDs
const { data } = db.useQuery({
  familyMessages: { $: { where: { memorialId: { $in: arrayOfIds } }, order: { serverCreatedAt: 'asc' } } }
})
```

---

## InstantDB Schema ‚Äî All Entities

Push schema: `npx instant-cli push schema` (from project root, reads `instant.schema.ts`)
Push perms:  `npx instant-cli push perms`  (reads `src/instant.perms.ts`)

The canonical app schema is at `src/instant.schema.ts`.
The root `instant.schema.ts` is kept in sync for the CLI ‚Äî **edit both if you add entities**.

### Entities & Key Fields

| Entity | Key Fields |
|---|---|
| `memorials` | `createdBy` (userId), `name`, `themeHex`, `alive`, `visibility`, `photo`, `coverPhoto` |
| `tributes` | `authorId`, `type` ('tribute' only), `content`, `photoUrl`, link ‚Üí memorial |
| `tributeComments` | `tributeId`, `memorialId`, `authorId`, `authorName`, `content`, `createdAt` |
| `profiles` | `userId`, `displayName`, `photoUrl`, `plan`, `onboarded` |
| `photos` | `url`, `takenAt` (EXIF/social Unix ms), `displayDate`, `source`, link ‚Üí memorial |
| `familyMembers` | `ownerId`, `memorialId`, `name`, `photo`, `ring` (1-3), `alive` |
| `invites` | `code` (8-char, indexed), `familyOwnerId`, `expiresAt`, `used` |
| `familyConnections` | `fromUserId`, `toMemorialId`, `toUserId`, `relation`, `status` ('pending'\|'approved'\|'rejected'), `verifyToken` (unique) |
| `familyMessages` | `memorialId`, `fromUserId`, `content`, `readBy` (JSON string[]) |
| `letters` | `createdBy`, `unlockType` ('date'\|'event'\|'immediate'), `isLocked` |
| `documents` | `createdBy`, `fileUrl`, `unlockType`, `isLocked` |
| `wills` | `testatorName`, `beneficiaries`, `executorName`, link ‚Üí memorial |

### Links (use `.link()` / include in query)
- `memorials` ‚Üí `tributes` (memorialTributes)
- `memorials` ‚Üí `photos` (memorialPhotos)
- `memorials` ‚Üí `letters` (memorialLetters)
- `memorials` ‚Üí `documents` (memorialDocuments)
- `memorials` ‚Üí `wills` (memorialWills)

