## Vault PIN ‚Äî Architecture

- PIN is 6 digits, never stored on any server
- On set: `SHA-256(pin + memorialId)` stored in `localStorage` as `vault_${memorialId}`
- On verify: `verifyPIN(memorialId, userId, plainPin)` in `src/lib/vaultAuth.js`
- On share: user re-enters plain PIN in `VaultShareModal`; verified client-side first;
  plain PIN sent to `/api/vault-share-pin` which emails it; PIN never persisted server-side
- On reset: `/api/vault-reset.js` requires identity proof (e.g. death certificate)

---

## CSS Conventions

- Tailwind v4 ‚Äî config is in CSS via `@theme` in `src/index.css`
- No `tailwind.config.js` ‚Äî all customisation in CSS
- Memorial theme colour via CSS custom properties:
  ```css
  --theme:    /* from memorial.themeHex, e.g. #92400e */
  --theme-lt: /* lighter tint */
  --theme-md: /* medium tint */
  ```
  Applied with `style={{ '--theme': memorial.themeHex, ... }}` on the page wrapper

---

## Photos ‚Äî Business Rules

- Max 5 photos per memorial (hard block on upload)
- EXIF date extracted on upload via `exifreader` ‚Äî stored as `takenAt` (Unix ms)
- `displayDate` is the human-readable string shown in the UI
- Photos sorted by `takenAt` ascending

---

## Family Connections ‚Äî Flow

1. Visitor clicks "Join as family" ‚Üí posts connection request ‚Üí `family-connection-request.js` emails owner
2. Owner sees pending request in dashboard ‚Üí Approve/Reject
3. On approve: `db.transact` updates `status: 'approved'` + `approvedAt` ‚Üí triggers `family-connection-approved.js` email
4. Approved member gains access to: Family tab, private messages, tribute comments, alive/deceased toggle, vault PIN sharing

---

## Environment Variables (Vercel Dashboard)

### Required for production
| Variable | Used in |
|---|---|
| `VITE_INSTANT_APP_ID` | Client ‚Äî InstantDB app ID |
| `VITE_CLOUDINARY_CLOUD_NAME` | Client ‚Äî Cloudinary cloud name |
| `RESEND_API_KEY` | `/api/` email functions |
| `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` | `/api/chat.js` |
| `ELEVENLABS_API_KEY` | `/api/elevenlabs.js` |
| `STRIPE_SECRET_KEY` | `/api/stripe.js`, `/api/stripe-webhook.js` |
| `STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET` | `/api/stripe-webhook.js` |
| `CLOUDINARY_API_SECRET` | `/api/memorial-pdf.js` (if signed upload) |
| `NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL` | `/api/` base URL fallback (set to `https://whowasi.uk`) |
| `INSTANT_APP_ADMIN_TOKEN` | `npx instant-cli` deploys (local only, not on Vercel) |

